    {
      "Text": "An update for pam is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules) is a system of libraries that handle the authentication tasks of applications (services) on the system.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nLinux-pam is a plug-in and unplugged system authentication software for Linux teams.\n There is a security vulnerability in Linux-pam. This vulnerability originates from insufficient protection when using user control paths by the pam_namespace module, which may cause local users to be elevated to root permissions through symbolic link attacks and race conditions.(CVE-2025-6020)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for pam is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
